Feature: VenuesDetailsVC UIKit redesign based on image1 (keep existing functions)

Overview
- Redesign `VenuesDetailsVC` visual layout using `.specify/features/SwiftUIFeatures/prototypes/venuesdetailsvc-redesign.prototype.html` as the primary review target, inspired by `.specify/features/SwiftUIFeatures/image1.png`.
- Keep the movie media area as a rectangular hero region.
- Introduce scroll-driven visual blur over the movie picture while user scrolls upward.
- Present details text area before action buttons.
- Align action buttons vertically.
- Preserve all existing function wiring and flows (`book`, `dates`, `map`, `movieDetail`, `selectCalendar`, `navigateBack`).

Scope
- In scope: `VenuesDetailsVC` layout hierarchy, spacing, visual states, and interaction polish.
- Out of scope: endpoint contracts, payload fields, auth headers, booking/payment logic, segue identifiers.

Functional requirements

REQ-VD-RD-1 Design baseline from reference
- `VenuesDetailsVC` must follow the hierarchy direction defined in `.specify/features/SwiftUIFeatures/prototypes/venuesdetailsvc-redesign.prototype.html`.
- `.specify/features/SwiftUIFeatures/image1.png` is the upstream visual inspiration.

REQ-VD-RD-2 Rectangular movie media region retained
- Movie media area remains a rectangle at the top region.
- Existing local video/image rendering strategy remains valid (no contract changes required).

REQ-VD-RD-3 Scroll-driven blur behavior
- A scrollable content layer can overlay the hero region while scrolling up.
- Blur intensity over movie picture increases with upward scroll progress.
- Blur effect must degrade gracefully if blur APIs are unavailable on target runtime.

REQ-VD-RD-4 Vertical content stack order
- Details text area appears before action controls.
- Action controls are vertically aligned in a single column.
- Required button set remains visible in redesigned order: `Book`, `Dates`, `Map`, `Movie Detail`, `Calendar`.

REQ-VD-RD-5 Preserve function contracts and navigation
- Existing button actions and segue routes remain unchanged.
- Existing data-manager interactions and request payload contracts remain unchanged.
- Existing hardcoded header/payload contracts remain untouched.

REQ-VD-RD-6 Back navigation retained
- Top/back navigation affordance remains available and visible.

REQ-VD-RD-7 Accessibility/readability
- Text remains readable across light/dark mode.
- Vertical button stack supports standard touch target sizing.

REQ-VD-RD-8 UIKit-only constraint
- Implementation must stay UIKit-based for this feature.
- Do not introduce SwiftUI wrappers/hosting for this scope.

Non-functional requirements

REQ-VD-RD-NF-1 Performance
- Scroll+blur behavior must remain smooth on supported devices.
- Redesign must not introduce repeated setup churn on repeated appearance transitions.

REQ-VD-RD-NF-2 Stability
- Existing booking/date/map/calendar/movie-detail flows continue to function unchanged.

REQ-VD-RD-9 Screen background and colors
- Screen background: white (#FFFFFF).
- Hero media area: rectangular, image/video fill with optional gradient overlay.
- Blur overlay (scroll state): semi-transparent dark (#000000) at 0-80% opacity based on scroll progress.
- Navigation buttons (Back): black (#000000), left-aligned in hero area top-left.
- Action buttons: full-width, black (#000000) background, white (#FFFFFF) text.
- Action button labels: use NSAttributedString with configurable font family + size.
- Details text area: black (#000000) text on white background.

REQ-VD-RD-10 Icon requirements
- Back button: left-pointing chevron (‹) or back arrow; 13px, black, semi-transparent background pill.
- Action button icons (left-aligned): Book (🎫 ticket), Dates (📅 calendar), Map (🗺️ map), Movie Detail (🎬 film), Calendar (📆 calendar); 12px each.
- Optional back affordance: subtle chevron indicator showing scroll-up gesture for hero media.
- Blur visual effect: iOS native `UIBlurEffect` or equivalent; Light/Dark adaptive.

Acceptance criteria
- [ ] Prototype exists at `.specify/features/SwiftUIFeatures/prototypes/venuesdetailsvc-redesign.prototype.html`.
- [ ] Prototype reflects rectangular hero media region and scroll-driven blur direction.
- [ ] Prototype shows details text before vertically aligned action buttons.
- [ ] Spec explicitly preserves existing VenuesDetailsVC function wiring and contracts.
- [ ] UIKit-only constraint documented.

Reference files
- `.specify/features/SwiftUIFeatures/prototypes/venuesdetailsvc-redesign.prototype.html`
- `.specify/features/SwiftUIFeatures/image1.png`
- `SwiftCinemas/SwiftLoginScreen/VenuesDetailsVC.swift`

